creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 152 by Various.
Read in English by Algy Pug; Bruce Kachuk; Son of the Exiles; Shakira Searle; Newgatenovelist; Karen Joan Kohoutek; Sonia; Tony Addison; John Burlinson; Winston Tharp; Fabiola; 5pak; Glenn O'Brien
This is a collection of 26 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for January 2016. It includes: Daisy, by Francis Thompson The Fallen Brave, by George Pope Morris The Green-Hand Rouseabout, by Henry Lawson Grown-up, by Edna St. Vincent Millay Is it Done?, by Ella Wheeler Wilcox Lines written after a very severe tempest which cleared up extremely pleasant, by Mercy Otis Warren Ne Plus Ultra, by Samuel Taylor Coleridge The Old Oaken Bucket, by Samuel Woodworth Othello - Iago, from Othello, Act. 3, Scene 3 (Part 1), by William Shakespeare Othello - Iago, from Othello, Act. 3, Scene 3 (Part 2), by William Shakespeare Other Days, by Lewis Morris The Painter on Silk, by Amy Lowell A Service of Song, by Emily Dickinson Seventy-Six, by George Pope Morris The Song of Courtesy, by George Meredith Sonnet 116, by William Shakespeare The Sword and the Staff, by George Pope Morris Sympathy, by Emily Brontë To a Friend, by Amy Lowell To the Unattainable: Lament of Mahomed Akram, by Laurence Hope What Do Poets Want With Gold?, by Archibald Lampman When You are Old, by William Butler Yeats The Wife of Bath's Tale, by Geoffrey Chaucer The Wife of Flanders, by G. K. Chesterton Winter Winds Cold and Blea, by John Clare The World is Full of Beauty, by Gerald Massey
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
